			</td><td width="2%">&nbsp;</td><td width="44%"> Abstract
			<div style="text-align:justify;">
				<P>
					<B>Introduction</B>: According to the Brazilian Association of Information Technology and Communication Companies (BRASSCOM, 2013), the information and communications technology market (ICT) moved in Brazil in 2012 the amount of 232 billion dollars, transforming the country 4th largest in the world ICT market. This sector, according to the Ministry of Development and Foreign Trade (MDIC, 2013) represents 7% of Brazil´s GDP and its growth rate is accelerated (10.8% from 2011 to 2012).
In Londrina the sector is also fairly representative. According to the prefecture, there are 468 companies in the city only Information Technology (LONDRINA, 2012). Adding to the business areas related to telecommunications, this figure reaches approximately 1,000, depending on the National Codes of Business Activities (CNAEs) considered to delimit the sector. In addition, other nearby cities to Londrina, arranged in the axis between Cornelius and Apucarana also have ICT companies.
However, although there lots of companies and organizations acting on behalf of the ICT sector, so far there is no survey to date information on the characteristics of firms and their respective market needs, so that it can implement planned actions and coordinated between the members of this production chain.					<B>Objectives</B>: The objective of the research is to identify the characteristics of information technology and communication companies of Londrina and the metropolitan area as the business segments , sizes , number of employees , market coverage , among other classificatory variables .
Among the variables , are also the tax environment for business , gross revenues and the opening time. With this research, seeks to profile the companies as well as understand what level it is this sector in Londrina region.					<B>Methods</B>: It is a survey of quantitative type, descriptive and cross-sectional, it aims to identify numerical information and depth of a given marketing phenomenon at some point this time.
Descriptive research has as objective to describe the characteristics of a population or phenomenon:
The research is descriptive, along with the exploration, those who normally carry out the partners concerned researchers with practical action. Also they are the most requested by organizations such as educational institutions, commercial companies, political parties, etc. (GIL. Descriptive Research. P.42. 2002)
Data were collected through a questionnaire self administered prepared with the Google Docs tool, whose link has been sent by email to companies. To encourage participants to respond, remained telephone contact with the companies in forming on the sending of e-mail and requesting filling out the form.
Quiz advantage is the time savings, and reach a lot of people, there is a certain freedom in the responses and greater uniformity in the assessment (Lakatos; MARCONI 1991)
To survey the number of ICT companies, a distance was delimited approximately 70 km around of Londrina, where the cities of:
Apucarana, Arapongas, Assam, Bela Vista do Paraiso, Camberley, Cornelius, Ibiporã, Jataizinho, Londrina, Rolândia, Sertanópolis and Uraí, among others smaller.
Using information from Londrina Development Company (CODEL) and the Internal Revenue Service identified the existence 1480 ICT companies in the aforementioned region.
Of these, pulled out a non-probabilistic convenience sample in order to get ideas on the subject of interest, so we collected information from 58 companies that responded to the survey, with most of them operating under more than one CNAE (National Code Economic activity), totaling 184 CNAES (confidence level 95% and 7% margin of error). (MATTAR 2001).
To achieve the objectives of this research, the following variables related to ICT companies will be analyzed:
a) tax framework.
b) Opening time.
c) Number of employees.
d) Your Business.
e) Gross revenue.					<B>Results</B>: 					<B>Conclusion</B>: 				</P>
